<task id="dg-validation-scenarios">
  <title>Configuring Validation Scenarios for a Framework</title>
  <titlealts>
    <navtitle>Validation Scenarios</navtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>Framework customization<indexterm>Configuring validation
          scenarios</indexterm></indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <taskbody>
    <context>
      <p id="p_tcb_dgk_54b">You can distribute a <xref keyref="glossentry_framework"><term>framework</term></xref> with
        a series of already configured validation scenarios. Also, this provides enhanced validation
        support that allows you to use multiple grammars to check the document. For example, you can
        use Schematron rules to impose guidelines that are otherwise impossible to enforce using
        conventional validation.<note conkeyref="reusables-editing-documents/validation-note" id="note_ucb_dgk_54b"/></p>
      <p id="p_vcb_dgk_54b">To associate a validation scenario with a specific <term>framework</term>, follow these
        steps:</p>
    </context>
    <steps>
      <step>
        <cmd><ph conkeyref="reusables-preferences-pages/Open-the-preferences-page"/> and go to
            <uicontrol>Document Type Association</uicontrol>.</cmd>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>Select the document type and click the <uicontrol>Edit</uicontrol> button to open the
            <xref href="the-document-type-dialog.dita#the-document-type-dialog"><uicontrol>Document
              Type Configuration</uicontrol> dialog box</xref>, then choose the
            <uicontrol>Validation</uicontrol> tab. This tab displays a list of document types. To
          set one or more of the validation scenarios listed in this tab to be used as the default
          validation scenario (when another one is not specified in the validation process) for a
          specific document type, check the <uicontrol>Default</uicontrol> box for that specific
          document type.</cmd>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>To edit an existing scenario, select the scenario and click the <uicontrol><image
              href="../img/Wrench16.png" id="image_v44_qyd_rlb"/>Edit</uicontrol> button. To add a
          new scenario, click the <uicontrol><image href="../img/Add16.png" id="image_b34_k3r_xr"
            />New</uicontrol> button.</cmd>
        <stepresult>In either case, a scenario configuration dialog box is displayed. It lists all
          the validation units for the scenario.<p id="p_wcb_dgk_54b">
            <fig id="figure-edit-validation-scenario-oxygen">
              <title>Validation Scenario Configuration Dialog Box</title>
              <image href="../img/sa_edit_validation_scenario_dialog.png" id="image_uss_w3r_xr"/>
            </fig>
          </p><p id="new-scenario-dialog-box">This scenario configuration dialog box allows you to
            configure the following information and options:<dl id="dl_xcb_dgk_54b">
              <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-validation-scenarios/name" id="dlentry_ycb_dgk_54b">
                <dt/>
                <dd/>
              </dlentry>
              <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-validation-scenarios/URL-of-file" id="dlentry_zcb_dgk_54b">
                <dt/>
                <dd/>
              </dlentry>
              <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-validation-scenarios/file-type" id="dlentry_adb_dgk_54b">
                <dt/>
                <dd/>
              </dlentry>
              <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-validation-scenarios/validation-engine" id="dlentry_bdb_dgk_54b">
                <dt/>
                <dd/>
              </dlentry>
              <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-validation-scenarios/automatic-validation" id="dlentry_cdb_dgk_54b">
                <dt/>
                <dd/>
              </dlentry>
              <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-validation-scenarios/schema" id="dlentry_ddb_dgk_54b">
                <dt/>
                <dd/>
              </dlentry>
              <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-validation-scenarios/settings" id="dlentry_xql_lbs_4pb">
                <dt/>
                <dd/>
              </dlentry>
              <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-validation-scenarios/move-up" id="dlentry_fdb_dgk_54b">
                <dt/>
                <dd/>
              </dlentry>
              <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-validation-scenarios/move-down" id="dlentry_gdb_dgk_54b">
                <dt/>
                <dd/>
              </dlentry>
              <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-validation-scenarios/add" id="dlentry_hdb_dgk_54b">
                <dt/>
                <dd/>
              </dlentry>
              <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-validation-scenarios/remove" id="dlentry_idb_dgk_54b">
                <dt/>
                <dd/>
              </dlentry>
            </dl></p></stepresult>
      </step>
      <step conkeyref="reusables-validation-scenarios/vs_7">
        <cmd/>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>Click <uicontrol>Ok</uicontrol>.</cmd>
        <stepresult>The newly created validation scenario is now included in the list of scenarios
          in the <xref href="document-type-validation-tab.dita#document-type-validation-tab"
              ><uicontrol>Validation</uicontrol> tab</xref>. You can use the
            <uicontrol>Default</uicontrol> checkbox to specify that the new scenario be used as the
          default validation scenario when another specific scenario is not specified in the
          validation process.</stepresult>
      </step>
    </steps>
  </taskbody>
